Savveyra v0.1.42_EventsDateTime_Stabilized_PreGroceriesRefresh

Events Date/Time Review and Stabilization

Database

* Confirmed Event Date/Time operational importance for multi-service events, production scheduling, and future grocery batching.
* Adopted Event DateTime as the authoritative event scheduling field.
* Backfilled existing Event records so Event DateTime is populated from legacy Event Date values.
* Updated vw_evt_items to expose:

  * event_datetime
  * event_time (derived)
  * event_datetime_display
* Added formatted display value:

  * YY-MM-DD | HH:mm

Events Page

* Corrected Event DateTime save behavior.
* Corrected Event DateTime reload behavior.
* Removed UTC conversion issues causing displayed time offsets.
* Verified Event DateTime persists correctly after save and page refresh.
* Verified Event DateTime reopens correctly after closing and reopening Events.
* Corrected dirty-state logic caused by DateTime timezone conversion mismatch.
* Save button now clears correctly after successful save.

Event Header

* Verified Event Ref saves and reloads correctly.
* Verified Total Guests saves correctly.
* Added missing default value binding for Total Guests input control.
* Confirmed Event header values reload correctly after save.

Event List

* Updated EventList query to include:

  * event_datetime
  * event_time
  * event_datetime_display
* Configured EventList to display formatted Date/Time value.
* Verified EventList displays correct local Event time.
* Hidden raw helper fields from user display:

  * event_date
  * event_time
  * event_datetime
* Retained helper fields in view for downstream use.

Operational Status

* Events DateTime architecture stabilized.
* Events save/load/display cycle validated.
* Dirty-state behavior validated.
* Ready to continue Groceries review and Update All propagation work from a stable Event scheduling foundation.

Next Focus

* Groceries
* Details
* Order
* Update All refresh architecture
* Event DateTime integration into Groceries workflow
